# Euclid Example: Linear Algebra

## Vectors

- Column vector: `$vector([x, y, z])$`
- Dot product: `$u dot v$`
- Norm: `$norm(v)$`
- Inner product: `$inner(u, v)$`

## Matrices

- Matrix literal: `$matrix([[a, b], [c, d]])$`
- Rotation matrix: `$matrix([cos(THETA), -sin(THETA)], [sin(THETA), cos(THETA)])$`
- Transpose and inverse: `$transpose(A) * inverse(A)$`

## Vector Calculus

- Gradient: `$grad(f)$`
- Divergence: `$divergence(F)$`
- Curl: `$curl(F)$`
